# SuperGit Debugging

## Enable debug

```json
{ "superGit.debug": true }
```

Logger: `src/logger.ts`. `info`/`warn`/`error` always log; `debug` only when setting is true.

Log file (typical): `~/.vscode-server/data/logs/<session>/exthost*/supergit.supergit/supergit.log`

Find latest:

```bash
find ~/.vscode-server/data/logs -path '*supergit.supergit/supergit.log' -type f -printf '%T@ %p\n' | sort -n | tail -1
```

Search narrowly (avoid broad `rg` over all VS Code logs):

```bash
rg -n "webview:|command invoked|creating SuperGit|error|warn|failed" ~/.vscode-server/data/logs/<session>/exthostN
```

## Symptom → check

| Symptom | Check |
|---------|-------|
| No status-bar button | `activationEvents`, status bar `command`, `remoteexthost.log` activation |
| Click does nothing | `command invoked {"command":"superGit.show"}` in logs |
| Stuck on "Loading Git graph..." | CSP, nonce, `scriptUri`, `localResourceRoots`; then React/JSX runtime |
| `html loaded` but no `bundle loaded` | Script blocked or failed to load |
| `bundle loaded` but no `app mounted` | React crash (often `React is not defined`) |
| `mounted` but no data | `webview message received {"type":"ready"}`; then Git/repo logs |
| `ready` but no commits | Repository root, `vscode.git` API, `src/git/runner.ts` logs, workspace is a git repo |
| Pull completed but tracking counts unchanged | Selected branch may not have been updated (non-checked-out `git pull` merges into current branch); confirm `branches loaded` after action |
| Refresh/prune feels slow or UI flickers | Count `loadInitialData start` and `refreshing after repository change` during one fetch — see `supergit-refresh-coordination.mdc` |
| First search/date change does nothing | Webview commit query-key sync in `App.tsx` — see `supergit-refresh-coordination.mdc` |
| Branch tracking buttons look white/unthemed | Global transparent `button` reset in `media/styles.css`; set dark backgrounds on `.local-branch-pill`, `.remote-row`, `.quick-button`, `.branch-list-item`, `.file-change-item` |
| Custom date picker calendar stays light in dark theme | Set `color-scheme` on `body.vscode-dark`/`vscode-light`; `.date-input` uses `--vscode-input-*` + `applyNativeColorScheme()` in `ThemeProvider` |

## UI failure checklist

Enable debug → reload → open SuperGit → `SuperGit: Show Logs` → confirm full stage chain through `commits loaded`, `branches loaded`, `remotes loaded`. On Branch History tab: `request-branch-history` → `branch-history-data`. Debug from the first missing stage.
